{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nThe allowlist drain (epic 716f) is removing every entry from `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt`. The FINAL split (reconcile.py) empties the allowlist to zero non-comment entries. That trips a latent bug in the CI `Module-size gate` shell (in both `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml` and `.github/workflows/test.yml`): the step runs under `bash -e -o pipefail`, and the line\n\n    listed=$(grep -vE '^[[:space:]]*(#|$)' \"$allowlist\" | awk '{print $1}' | sort -u)\n\nmakes `grep` return exit 1 when the allowlist has NO non-comment lines (no match), which under `pipefail`+`set -e` aborts the whole step with exit 1 BEFORE the over-cap check runs. Reproduced locally against the drained tree (the step exits 1 right after printing 'Allow-listed files (ceiling ratchet):'). Because the gate runs from main's workflow against each change's tree, this fix MUST land on main BEFORE the allowlist-emptying change (reconcile) can pass Verified.\n\n## What\n\nApply the SAME one-line guard to the `listed=` line in BOTH `.github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml` and `.github/workflows/test.yml`, so a no-match grep does not abort the step (behavior identical for a non-empty allowlist):\n\n    listed=$({ grep -vE '^[[:space:]]*(#|$)' \"$allowlist\" || true; } | awk '{print $1}' | sort -u)\n\nThat specific `listed=` line IS currently identical in both files, so it is the same edit in each. NOTE (verified against the current code): the two Module-size gate step BODIES are NOT otherwise byte-identical — `test.yml` uses a more verbose per-file error printout in the `if [ -n \"$new_offenders\" ]` block than `gerrit-verify.yaml` does — but that pre-existing divergence is unrelated to this fix and is left UNCHANGED. This change only edits the shared `listed=` line (plus a 3-line explanatory comment above it) in each file; it does not touch the divergent error-printout lines and does not attempt to harmonize the bodies. The parity test `tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py` asserts both workflows contain the same NAMED gate steps (catching a gate present in only one) — it does NOT diff step bodies — so it stays green.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Both workflow files contain the guarded form of the line (verify: `grep -c '{ grep -vE .* || true; } | awk' .github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml .github/workflows/test.yml` reports 1 for each file, and `! grep -qE 'listed=\\$\\(grep -vE' .github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml .github/workflows/test.yml` — the un-guarded form is gone from both)\n- [ ] Running the gate shell against a zero-entry (comment-only) allowlist runs to completion instead of aborting at the grep — with no over-cap files it prints 'Module-size gate: OK' and exits 0 (verify: extract the gate step and run it against a comment-only allowlist + a src tree with no over-cap file)\n- [ ] The gate still FAILS when a non-allow-listed file exceeds 800 LOC — behavior preserved for the non-empty case (verify: run the gate against an allowlist missing an over-cap file → exit 1)\n- [ ] `tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py` passes — the 'Module-size gate' step remains present in BOTH workflows (verify: `pytest tests/unit/test_ci_workflow_parity.py -q`)\n\n## Notes\nSmall CI-shell robustness fix scoped to ONE line per file. E5 testing-plan: satisfied by the parity test + the manual gate-shell exercises named in the ACs (the gate is shell, so the oracle is running the shell against crafted allowlist/tree fixtures). This change does NOT modify the allowlist itself (reconcile.py stays listed), so main's current gate passes on it."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784413946448579001,"uuid":"cee16364-3b45-4d60-84d1-4641e915ceaf"}